# EDAMAME Foundation - Core Library

> **Master Repository:** `edamame_app` - See `../edamame_app/.cursor/rules/workspace.mdc` for workspace-wide rules.

## Documentation (Read First)
- **CLAUDE.md** - Build commands, testing, architecture overview
- **ARCHITECTURE.md** - Helper protocol, threat model system, scoring
- **README.md** - Library overview and ecosystem

## Project Context
EDAMAME Foundation provides:
- Helper protocol (gRPC IPC with privileged daemon)
- Threat assessment engine with platform-specific metrics
- Security scoring algorithm
- Network analysis integration (via flodbadd)

## Key Files
- `src/helper_rx.rs` - Server-side helper implementation
- `src/helper_tx.rs` - Client-side helper interface
- `src/threat.rs` - Core threat model structures
- `src/threat_metrics_*.rs` - Platform-specific security checks
- `src/score.rs` - Security score calculation

## Build & Test
```bash
cargo build --features packetcapture
cargo test --features packetcapture -- --nocapture
```

## Code Patterns
- Helper protocol uses Protocol Buffers (`proto/edamame.proto`)
- Threat metrics are JSON-defined in `edamame_models` repo
- Order types: `metricorder` (security ops) and `utilityorder` (system ops)
- Platform detection via `#[cfg(target_os = "...")]`

## Local Development
Toggle local/git dependencies (run from edamame_app):
```bash
cd ../edamame_app && ./flip.sh local
cd ../edamame_app && ./flip.sh git
```
